  = section "The Imperfect Tense" do
    %p The imperfect tense is formed by adding the regular passive endings (with -a- rather than -e- in the  first and second person) to the stem #{template "*C1uC2C2aC3-"}, or #{template "*C1əC2aC3-"} if #{template "C2"} surfaces as an aspirate. If #{template "C3"} can undergo lenition, it does so in all of the first and second person forms.
