  = section "The Perfective Subjunctive Tense" do
    %p The perfective subjunctive is formed by adding a special set of prefixes to the stem #{template "*-C1əC2C2aC3"}, replacing gemination with aspiration if appropriate. As with the present tense, the prefixes have been modified to reinstate the passive /u/ that was lost before aspirate consonants, with *vu- in the first person singular, *vanū- in the first person plural, *vatū- in the second person, and the unchanged *vē in the third person.
