= section "Geminate Roots and kəthāb" do
  %p Geminate roots conjugate as though they were triconsonantal, with the geminate root consonant split into two single consonants. The root *dall “be humble”, for instance, becomes #{t "δαλλώλ", "dəllāl"} “be tamed, subdued, subjugated”:
